<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1894-08-01T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1894-08-01T00:00:00-05:00" n="228" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d228">
                        <head><hi rend="italic">Mr. <persName type="from">Gresham</persName> to
                                Messrs. <persName type="to">Goodrich, Beady &amp;
                                    Goodrich</persName></hi>.</head>
                        <opener><dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Department of State</hi>,<lb/><hi rend="italic">Washington</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1894-08-01"><hi rend="italic">August 1,
                                1894</hi></date>.</dateline></opener>
                        <p><hi rend="smallcaps">Gentlemen</hi>: Your letter of the 26th ultimo, and
                            the affidavit of Mr. A. F. Stubbs, have been examined in connection with
                            the papers already on file here relative to the schooner <hi rend="italic">Henry Crosby</hi>, and in reply I have to say that I
                            see no reason to change the opinion expressed in the Department’s letter
                            to you under date of April 10 last.</p>
                        <p>I am, etc.,</p>
                        <closer><signed><hi rend="smallcaps">W. Q. Gresham</hi></signed>.</closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>